SUMMARY:I Don't Know What I'm Doing: A Newbie Guide for Golang for DevOps
ORGANIZER:Peter Souter
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181231T000000Z
DTSTART:20190204T150000Z
DTEND:20190204T155500Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Golang as a language has exploded with popularity since it&rsquo;s first release in 2009.<br />
It&rsquo;s now the langauage behind a number of applications core to most organisations operations, such as Docker, Terraform, Kubernetes and etcd.</p>

<p>However, for most people used to scripting interpreted languages like Ruby and Python,
it can be a bit hard to get started with. What&rsquo;s all this err != nil business, and why am I getting errors when I don&rsquo;t refer to a variable?</p>

<p>In this talk, we&rsquo;ll be discussing how to learn enough Golang to get into trouble,
or at least enough to contribute fixes and features to your favourite infra management tools and apps,
with an example of adding a new feature to the Vault Terraform Provider, and the gotcha&rsquo;s you might experience along the way.</p>

